main event: A military report noted the observation of one unidentified flying object, potentially a satellite, on 18 November 1964.
interesting points: The object was bright, comparable to a first magnitude star., Initial observation at an elevation of 10 degrees, which descended to the horizon., The observation lasted for about 10 minutes., The object was believed to be reflecting off the Echo II satellite., At 110 degrees azimuth, the object faded from view.
sighted object: one unidentified flying object, possibly a satellite
witness description: Military source; no specific witnesses mentioned
